The paper deals with reasoning about resource usages in distributed applications, which involves modeling resources as entities with local policies and global properties. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions developing a Control Flow Analysis to compute a static approximation of process behavior, which is a common technique in Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on resource management and interactions between local and global information suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
